def: The state behind or past. [Obs.]In the dark backward and abysm of time. Shak.
The act or process of volatilizing, or rendering volatile; thestate of being volatilized.
Hardihood; boldness; courage; energetic action. [Obs.]Changing hardiment with great Glendower. Shak.

To form with short turns, bends, or wrinkles; to mold intoinequalites or sinuosities; to cause to wrinkle or curl.The houscrinkled to and fro. Chaucer.Her face all bowsy, Comely crinkled, Wondrously wrinkled. Skelton.The flames through all the casements pushing forth, Like red-notdevils crinkled into snakes. Mrs. Browning.
The state of being inaquate. [Obs.] Bp. Gardiner.
The exact opposite.The German prose offers the counterpole to the French style. DeQuincey.
To know or perceive; to recognize.The reasoning faculty can deal with no facts until they are cognizedby it. H. Spencer.
Having floral ornaments; as, floriated capitals of Gothicpillars.
The quality an apron can hold.
